\begin_layout Standard
(c) Moana's utility maximization problem
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{d,f}{max}U(d,f)=df
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
subject to: 
\begin_inset Formula $g(d,f)=100d+400f-4000=0$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Lagrangian function: 
\begin_inset Formula $\Lambda(d,f,\lambda)=U(d,f)+\lambda g(d,f)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=df+\lambda(100d+400f-4000)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Solving Lagrangian function:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
\frac{\delta\Lambda}{\delta d}=f+100\lambda & =0\\
\frac{\delta\Lambda}{\delta f}=d+400\lambda & =0\\
\frac{\delta\Lambda}{\delta\lambda}=100d+400f-4000 & =0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
4(f+100\lambda) & =0\\
d+400\lambda & =0\\
100d+400f-4000 & =0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
d-4f & =0\\
d+400\lambda & =0\\
100d+400f-4000 & =0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
d & =20\\
f & =5\\
\lambda & =-0.05
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Question 3
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(a) 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{x,y}{max}U(x,y)=\sqrt{xy}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
subject to: 
\begin_inset Formula $g(x,y)=4x+4y-400=0$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Lagrangian function: 
\begin_inset Formula $\Lambda(x,y,\lambda)=U(x,y)+\lambda g(x,y)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\sqrt{xy}+\lambda(4x+4y-400)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Solving Lagrangian function:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
\frac{\delta\Lambda}{\delta x}=\frac{1}{2}\sqrt{\frac{y}{x}}+4\lambda & =0\\
\frac{\delta\Lambda}{\delta y}=\frac{1}{2}\sqrt{\frac{x}{y}}+4\lambda & =0\\
\frac{\delta\Lambda}{\delta\lambda}=4x+4y-400 & =0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
\frac{1}{2}\sqrt{\frac{y}{x}}-\frac{1}{2}\sqrt{\frac{x}{y}} & =0\\
\frac{1}{2}\sqrt{\frac{x}{y}}+4\lambda & =0\\
4x+4y-400 & =0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
\sqrt{\frac{y}{x}} & =\sqrt{\frac{x}{y}}\\
\lambda & =-\frac{1}{8}\sqrt{\frac{x}{y}}\\
4x+4y-400 & =0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
x & =y\\
\lambda & =-\frac{1}{8}\sqrt{\frac{x}{y}}\\
4x+4y-400 & =0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
x & =y\\
\lambda & =-\frac{1}{8}\sqrt{\frac{x}{y}}\\
4x+4y-400 & =0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
\lambda & =-0.125\\
x & =50\\
y & =50
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(b)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{x,y}{max}U(x,y)=\sqrt{xy}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
subject to: 
\begin_inset Formula $g(x,y)=4x+4y-720=0$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Using the same process in (a)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
\lambda & =-0.125\\
x & =90\\
y & =90
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(c)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{x,y}{max}U(x,y)=\sqrt{xy}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
subject to: 
\begin_inset Formula $\begin{cases}
4x+4y-720=0 & x\geq80\\
4y=100 & x<80
\end{cases}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hypothetically 
\begin_inset Formula $x\ge80$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Solve similarly to (b):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
\lambda & =-0.125\\
x & =90\\
y & =90
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hypothesis is satisfied, accepting this basket as optimal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(d) With the cash subsidy:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{x,y}{max}U(x,y)=\sqrt{xy}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
subject to: 
\begin_inset Formula $g(x,y)=4x+4y-880=0$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Solve the optimization using Lagrage's method:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
\lambda & =-0.125\\
x & =110\\
y & =110
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U(x,y)_{cash}=110
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With the coconut (x) voucher:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{x,y}{max}U(x,y)=\sqrt{xy}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
subject to: 
\begin_inset Formula $\begin{cases}
4x+4y-880=0 & x\geq120\\
4y=100 & x<120
\end{cases}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Assuming 
\begin_inset Formula $x\ge120$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Solve the optimization using Lagrage's method:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
\lambda & =-0.125\\
x & =110\\
y & =110
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Assumption not satisfied, optimal basket occurs at 
\begin_inset Formula $x=120$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Rightarrow\begin{cases}
x & =120\\
4x+4y-880 & =0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
x & =120\\
y & =100
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U(x,y)_{voucher}=109.55
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore, Pue's optimal utility of when given cash subsity is greater than
 coconut voucher
\end_layout

